# Accessibility Rules

## Standards
WCAG 2.1 Level AA on all pages and components.

## HTML
- Semantic elements: `nav`, `main`, `article`, `section`, `header`, `footer`
- One `<h1>` per page; no heading level skips
- Skip-to-content link in root layout

## Interactive
- All elements keyboard accessible with visible focus (`focus-visible:ring-2`)
- Buttons not divs; form inputs have `<label>` elements
- Modal: focus trap + Escape to close
- Mobile menu: `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`

## Motion
```typescript
const prefersReducedMotion = useReducedMotion();
// Disable animations when true
```

## Forms
- `aria-invalid="true"` on error fields
- `aria-describedby` linking to error messages
- Server-side validation with Zod (client validation is UX only)

## Images
- Alt text from WordPress `altText` field; empty alt for decorative images
